---
description: Platform-specific file conventions
globs:
  - "internal/**/*_linux.go"
  - "internal/**/*_darwin.go"
  - "internal/**/*_windows.go"
  - "internal/**/*_freebsd.go"
  - "internal/**/*_fallback.go"
---
When editing platform-specific files:

- Every platform file must have a `//go:build <os>` tag at the top.
- Always provide a `_fallback.go` file for unsupported platforms.
- Never add plaintext URLs; all network fetches must be HTTPS.
- Never execute downloaded content directly.
- Keep platform logic isolated; share types and interfaces from non-platform files.
